    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-11-09T04:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-11-09T04:00:00-05:00" n="729"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d729">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/11035: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Counselor of Embassy in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lockhart</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-11-09T17:00:00+08:00"
                            >November 9, 1937—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received November 9—5:55 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>738. Embassy’s 735, November 8, 4 p.m.</p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>The local Japanese spokesman has announced that the Japanese occupation of
                        Taiyuan was completed this morning.</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>Press reports indicate that Changteh in northern Honan on the
                        Peiping–Hankow Railroad is now occupied by the Japanese (Embassy’s 728,
                        November 5, 4 p.m.<note n="5" xml:id="d729fn5">Not printed.</note>)</item>
                </list>
                <p>Repeated to Nanking, by courier to Tokyo.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lockhart</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
